#: ../../../gpu_configuration.rst:8
msgid "Using External GPU Support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu_configuration.rst:10
msgid ""
"Many packages come with a ``+cuda`` or ``+rocm`` variant. With no added "
"configuration Spack will download and install the needed components. It may "
"be preferable to use existing system support: the following sections help "
"with using a system installation of GPU libraries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu_configuration.rst:17
msgid "Using an External ROCm Installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu_configuration.rst:19
msgid ""
"Spack breaks down ROCm into many separate component packages. The following "
"is an example ``packages.yaml`` that organizes a consistent set of ROCm "
"components for use by dependent packages:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu_configuration.rst:23
msgid ""
"packages:\n"
"  all:\n"
"    compiler: [rocmcc@=5.3.0]\n"
"    variants: amdgpu_target=gfx90a\n"
"  hip:\n"
"    buildable: false\n"
"    externals:\n"
"    - spec: hip@5.3.0\n"
"      prefix: /opt/rocm-5.3.0/hip\n"
"  hsa-rocr-dev:\n"
"    buildable: false\n"
"    externals:\n"
"    - spec: hsa-rocr-dev@5.3.0\n"
"      prefix: /opt/rocm-5.3.0/\n"
"  llvm-amdgpu:\n"
"    buildable: false\n"
"    externals:\n"
"    - spec: llvm-amdgpu@5.3.0\n"
"      prefix: /opt/rocm-5.3.0/llvm/\n"
"  comgr:\n"
"    buildable: false\n"
"    externals:\n"
"    - spec: comgr@5.3.0\n"
"      prefix: /opt/rocm-5.3.0/\n"
"  hipsparse:\n"
"    buildable: false\n"
"    externals:\n"
"    - spec: hipsparse@5.3.0\n"
"      prefix: /opt/rocm-5.3.0/\n"
"  hipblas:\n"
"    buildable: false\n"
"    externals:\n"
"    - spec: hipblas@5.3.0\n"
"      prefix: /opt/rocm-5.3.0/\n"
"  rocblas:\n"
"    buildable: false\n"
"    externals:\n"
"    - spec: rocblas@5.3.0\n"
"      prefix: /opt/rocm-5.3.0/\n"
"  rocprim:\n"
"    buildable: false\n"
"    externals:\n"
"    - spec: rocprim@5.3.0\n"
"      prefix: /opt/rocm-5.3.0/rocprim/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu_configuration.rst:70
msgid "This is in combination with the following compiler definition:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu_configuration.rst:72
msgid ""
"compilers:\n"
"- compiler:\n"
"    spec: rocmcc@=5.3.0\n"
"    paths:\n"
"      cc: /opt/rocm-5.3.0/bin/amdclang\n"
"      cxx: /opt/rocm-5.3.0/bin/amdclang++\n"
"      f77: null\n"
"      fc: /opt/rocm-5.3.0/bin/amdflang\n"
"    operating_system: rhel8\n"
"    target: x86_64"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu_configuration.rst:85
msgid "This includes the following considerations:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu_configuration.rst:87
msgid ""
"Each of the listed externals specifies ``buildable: false`` to force Spack "
"to use only the externals we defined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu_configuration.rst:89
msgid ""
"``spack external find`` can automatically locate some of the ``hip``/"
"``rocm`` packages, but not all of them, and furthermore not in a manner that "
"guarantees a complementary set if multiple ROCm installations are available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu_configuration.rst:92
msgid ""
"The ``prefix`` is the same for several components, but note that others "
"require listing one of the subdirectories as a prefix."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu_configuration.rst:97
msgid "Using an External CUDA Installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu_configuration.rst:99
msgid "CUDA is split into fewer components and is simpler to specify:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu_configuration.rst:101
msgid ""
"packages:\n"
"  all:\n"
"    variants:\n"
"    - cuda_arch=70\n"
"  cuda:\n"
"    buildable: false\n"
"    externals:\n"
"    - spec: cuda@11.0.2\n"
"      prefix: /opt/cuda/cuda-11.0.2/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu_configuration.rst:113
msgid "where ``/opt/cuda/cuda-11.0.2/lib/`` contains ``libcudart.so``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu_configuration.rst:119
msgid "Using an External OpenGL API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu_configuration.rst:120
msgid ""
"Depending on whether we have a graphics card or not, we may choose to use "
"OSMesa or GLX to implement the OpenGL API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu_configuration.rst:122
msgid ""
"If a graphics card is unavailable, OSMesa is recommended and can typically "
"be built with Spack. However, if we prefer to utilize the system GLX "
"tailored to our graphics card, we need to declare it as an external. Here's "
"how to do it:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu_configuration.rst:126
msgid ""
"packages:\n"
"  libglx:\n"
"    require: [opengl]\n"
"  opengl:\n"
"    buildable: false\n"
"    externals:\n"
"    - prefix: /usr/\n"
"      spec: opengl@4.6"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu_configuration.rst:137
msgid ""
"Note that prefix has to be the root of both the libraries and the headers, "
"using is /usr not the path the the lib. To know which spec for opengl is "
"available use ``cd /usr/include/GL && grep -Ri gl_version``."
msgstr ""
